07f8449af.transcription-guidelines:
- Normalisation of «V» to «U» except in Latin inscriptions;
- Preservation of the diacritical marks and punctuation as used by the Author except for the part in Greek;
- Where the use of capital and small caps is not distinguished, it is transcribed according to the grammatical rules of the Italian language;
- Tagging of uncertain words with the «unclear» tag;
- Tagging of illegible words with three dots (...) and the «unclear» tag;
- Use of the angle dash, instead of the hyphen, to divide words into syllables at the end of a line.
Moreover due to some issues in the visualization of ancient symbols unicode, the Roman Denarius (U+10196) and the Roman Sestersius (U+10198) signs were transcribed using other symbols not used by the author from the Astronomical chart:
Roman denarius sign ➛♀(U+2640 Female sign)
Roman sestertius sign➛☿ (U+263F Mercury)
In order to change them to the correct one during post-processing.

